Isaiah 1-8 <t>And <f>ⓤ</f>the daughter of Zion is left </t><t>like a <f>ⓥ</f>booth in a vineyard, </t><t>like a lodge in a cucumber field, </t><t>like a besieged city. </t>
Isaiah 1-9 <pb/><t><f>ⓦ</f> If the LORD of hosts </t><t>had not left us <f>ⓧ</f>a few survivors, </t><t>we should have been like <f>ⓨ</f>Sodom, </t><t>and become like <f>ⓩ</f>Gomorrah. </t>
