Isaiah 1-14 <t>Your <f>ⓙ</f>new moons and your appointed feasts </t><t>my soul hates; </t><t>they have become a burden to me; </t><t>I am weary of bearing them.</t>
Isaiah 1-15 <t>When you <f>ⓚ</f>spread out your hands, </t><t>I will hide my eyes from you; </t><t><f>ⓛ</f>even though you make many prayers, </t><t>I will not listen; </t><t><f>ⓜ</f>your hands are full of blood.</t>
Isaiah 1-16 <t><f>ⓝ</f> Wash yourselves; make yourselves clean; </t><t>remove the evil of your deeds from before my eyes; </t><t><f>ⓞ</f>cease to do evil,</t>
